<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koukouras, Athanasios" journalOrPublisher="Cahiers de Biologie Marine" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="301 - 319" title="Benthic bionomy of the North Aegean Sea III. A comparison of the macrobenthic animal assemblages associated with seven sponge species." volume="26" year="1985">Koukouras et al. (1985)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Simboura, N" journalOrPublisher="National and Kapodistrian University of Athens, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Study of the distribution and variations of the benthic polychaete fauna in three regions of the Aegean Sea and especially in the Island of Rhodes. MSc thesis" year="1987">Simboura (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. In the Mediterranean also known from France (
<bibRefCitation author="Bellan, Gerard" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Universite d'Aix-Marseille, Marseille" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Contribution a l'etude systematique, bionomique et ecologique des Annelides Polychetes de la Mediterrannee" year="1964">Bellan 1964a</bibRefCitation>
), Spain (
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez, J" editor="Vieitez, J. M." journalOrPublisher="Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Annelida, Polychaeta I. In: Ramos MA, Alba J, Belles X, Gosalbez J, Guerra A, Macpherson E, Martin F, Serrano J, Templado J (Eds.) Fauna Iberica" year="2004">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Núñez">Nunez</normalizedToken>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
) and Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Castelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Biologia Marina Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="323 - 373" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta" volume="15" year="2008">Castelli et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), otherwise distributed along the Atlantic coasts of Europe and North Africa. Italian records are, however, considered questionable by 
<bibRefCitation author="Castelli, A" journalOrPublisher="Biologia Marina Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="323 - 373" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta" volume="15" year="2008">Castelli et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
as the species is easily confused with 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Perinereis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Perinereis rullieri" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="rullieri">Perinereis rullieri</taxonomicName>
Pilato, 1974.
</paragraph>
